  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1:40-45 We have here Christ's cleansing of a leper. It teaches us to apply to the Saviour with great humility, and with full submission to his will, saying, Lord, if thou wilt, without any doubt of Christ's readiness to help the distressed. See also what to expect from Christ; that according to our faith it shall be to us. The poor leper said, If thou wilt. Christ readily wills favours to those who readily refer themselves to his will. Christ would have nothing done that looked like seeking praise of the people. But no reasons now exist why we should hesitate to spread the praises of Christ.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And there came a leper ... - See the notes at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 8:1-4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Kneeling down to him - He kneeled and inclined his face to the ground, in token of deep humiliation and earnest entreaty. Compare Luke 5:12.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Kneeling down to him - He kneeled and inclined his face to the ground, in token of deep humiliation and earnest entreaty. Compare ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Luke 5:12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "If thou wilt - This was an acknowledgment of the almighty power of Jesus, and an appeal to his benevolence.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Make me clean - You (Jesus) can heal me of this loathsome and offensive disease, in the eye of the law justly regarded as \"unclean,\" and render me \"legally\" clean, and restore me to the privileges of the congregation.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And Jesus ...touched him - It was by the law considered as unclean to touch a leprous man. See Numbers 5:2. The fact that Jesus touched him was evidence that the requisite power had been already put forth to heal him; that Jesus regarded him as already clean.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "And Jesus ...touched him - It was by the law considered as unclean to touch a leprous man. See ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 5:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The fact that Jesus touched him was evidence that the requisite power had been already put forth to heal him; that Jesus regarded him as already clean.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "I will - Here was a most manifest proof of his divine power. None but God can work a miracle; yet Jesus does it by his \"own will\" - by an exertion of his own power. Therefore, Jesus is divine.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "See thou say nothing to any man - The law of Moses required that a man who was healed of the leprosy should be pronounced clean by the priest before he could be admitted again to the privileges of the congregation, Leviticus 14. Christ, though he had cleansed him, yet required him to be obedient to the law of the land - to go at once to the priest, and not to make delay by stopping to converse about his being healed. It was also possible that, if he did not go at once, evil-minded men would go before him and prejudice the priest, and prevent his declaring the healing to be thorough because it was done by Jesus. It was of further importance that \"the priest\" should pronounce it to be a genuine cure, that there might be no cavils among the Jews against its being a real miracle.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "See thou say nothing to any man - The law of Moses required that a man who was healed of the leprosy should be pronounced clean by the priest before he could be admitted again to the privileges of the congregation, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Leviticus 14",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". Christ, though he had cleansed him, yet required him to be obedient to the law of the land - to go at once to the priest, and not to make delay by stopping to converse about his being healed. It was also possible that, if he did not go at once, evil-minded men would go before him and prejudice the priest, and prevent his declaring the healing to be thorough because it was done by Jesus. It was of further importance that \"the priest\" should pronounce it to be a genuine cure, that there might be no cavils among the Jews against its being a real miracle.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Offer for thy cleansing those things ... - Two birds, and cedar-wood, and scarlet, and hyssop; and after eight days, two he-lambs, without blemish, and one ewe-lamb, and fine flour, and oil, Leviticus 14:4, Leviticus 14:10.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Offer for thy cleansing those things ... - Two birds, and cedar-wood, and scarlet, and hyssop; and after eight days, two he-lambs, without blemish, and one ewe-lamb, and fine flour, and oil, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Leviticus 14:4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Leviticus 14:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For a testimony unto them - Not to the priest, but to the people, that they may have evidence that it is a real cure. The testimony of the priest on the subject would be decisive.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "For a testimony unto them - Not to the priest, but to the people, that they may have evidence that it is a real cure. The testimony of the priest on the subject would be decisive.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
